    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect MCS selection due to UE network capability decoding bug\n\n### Summary\nThe `decode_ue_network_capability` function in UeNetworkCapability.c contained faulty logic that incorrectly adjusted the decoded length, causing the function to return wrong values. This led to improper parsing of UE network capabilities which in turn affected MCS table selection decisions.\n\nThe issue was particularly evident when UEs with specific capability combinations connected, resulting in suboptimal MCS selection that didn't match the UE's actual capabilities.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/UeNetworkCapability.c`: Removed incorrect decoded length adjustment logic that was causing the function to return wrong byte counts. The function now correctly returns the actual number of bytes consumed from the input buffer, matching the behavior of similar decoding functions.\n\nUsers may observe improved MCS selection accuracy after this fix, especially with UEs that report specific network capability combinations. Prior to this fix, some UEs might have been assigned lower MCS values than optimal due to incorrectly parsed capability information.\n"
}